Narelle Kheng (born 24 September 1993) is a Singaporean musician, actress, presenter, and former national swimmer.
In 2012, she made her debut in the Singaporean band The Sam Willows.
After announcing their hiatus in May 2019, she has since pursued her solo career.
Narelle released her solo single “Outta My Head” on April 4, 2019.
She released her debut EP “Part 2” on October 10, 2019, in conjunction with World Mental Health Day.
